  },
  {
    question: "What warranty does DrySpace provide on Markham waterproofing?",
    answer: "We provide a 25-year fully transferable warranty on all exterior waterproofing work in Markham, covering materials and workmanship. Interior drainage systems include a 25-year warranty on the system and lifetime warranty on our cast-iron sump pumps. The warranty covers any water intrusion related to our installed systems and transfers to new homeowners if you sell. For Markham's challenging clay soil conditions and seasonal water table fluctuations, we stand behind our work with regular follow-up inspections and responsive service if any issues arise."
  },
  {
    question: "How do subdivision drainage issues affect individual Markham homes?",
    answer: "Many Markham subdivisions have interconnected drainage where multiple properties share storm sewers and drainage routes. This means your basement water problems might stem from: neighbors' lots draining toward your foundation, municipal storm sewers backing up during heavy rain, subdivision grading that directs water incorrectly, or shared drainage tiles that are clogged. We assess the entire drainage context around your Markham home, not just your foundation. Solutions often include grading corrections, independent sump discharge to street, and interior backup systems to handle excess water when subdivision drainage is overwhelmed during storms."
  },
  {
    question: "When is the best time to waterproof a basement in Markham?",
    answer: "Late spring through fall (May-November) is ideal for exterior waterproofing in Markham, as frozen ground prevents winter excavation. However, don't wait if you have active leaks. We provide emergency repairs year-round and can perform interior drainage installation in any season. For Markham's Rouge River flood zone homes, we recommend scheduling work in summer after spring flooding but before fall rains. Many Markham homeowners plan projects after spring water incidents while the problem is fresh. Book early as we're busiest in May-June when water damage is most visible."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I get rebates for basement waterproofing in Markham?",
    answer: "York Region offers various rebates and programs including the Residential Flood Protection Subsidy (up to $3,400 for eligible homeowners), Ontario Seniors Home Renovation Tax Credit (up to $1,500 annually for those 65+), and potential home insurance premium reductions after waterproofing. Some neighbourhood improvement area programs in Markham provide additional grants for heritage properties in Unionville. We help Markham homeowners identify and apply for all available rebates and provide the documentation needed for insurance discounts. Total savings can offset 15-25% of project costs."
  },
  {
    question: "How do you handle Markham's dense clay soil conditions?",
    answer: "Markham's heavy clay soil is one of the most challenging in the GTA for waterproofing. Clay holds water, swells when wet, creates high hydrostatic pressure, and makes excavation difficult. Our Markham-specific approach includes: heavy equipment suitable for clay excavation, proper stone bedding under drainage tile (not just backfill with clay), reinforced waterproofing membranes to handle pressure, sump pump systems sized for clay's slow drainage characteristics, and soil amendments when backfilling. We've completed over 400 projects in Markham's clay conditions and know exactly how to build systems that perform long-term despite soil challenges."
  },
  {
    question: "Is basement waterproofing in Markham covered by insurance?",
    answer: "Standard home insurance typically doesn't cover waterproofing or gradual water seepage, but may cover sudden damage from sewer backup or foundation collapse. However, many Markham homeowners find that investing in professional waterproofing qualifies them for overland flood insurance (increasingly important near Rouge River) and reduces premiums on water damage coverage. Some insurers offer discounts of 5-15% after waterproofing installation. We provide detailed invoices and warranties that satisfy insurance requirements for premium reductions and can document work for insurance claims if water damage occurred before waterproofing."
