  {
    question: "How long does basement waterproofing take in Markham?",
    answer: "Exterior waterproofing in Markham typically takes 3-5 days for an average home, depending on foundation length and clay soil conditions (which slow excavation). Interior drainage systems can be completed in 1-2 days. Timelines include: permit processing (1-2 weeks), excavation and foundation prep (1-2 days in clay soil), membrane and drainage installation (1-2 days), backfill and site restoration (1 day). For Markham subdivisions with tight property access or heritage Unionville homes requiring careful work, projects may take longer. We provide detailed schedules and work efficiently to minimize disruption to your Markham home."
